51cricket::PortInterface::CandidateOrigin GetOrigin(
52 cricket::PortInterface* port,
53 cricket::PortInterface* origin_port) {
54 if (!origin_port)
55 return cricket::PortInterface::ORIGIN_MESSAGE;
56 else if (port == origin_port)
57 return cricket::PortInterface::ORIGIN_THIS_PORT;
58 else
59 return cricket::PortInterface::ORIGIN_OTHER_PORT;
60}

62uint32_t GetWeakPingIntervalInFieldTrial() {
63 uint32_t weak_ping_interval = ::strtoul(
64 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-StunInterPacketDelay").c_str(),
65 nullptr, 10);
66 if (weak_ping_interval) {
67 return static_cast<int>(weak_ping_interval);
68 }
69 return cricket::WEAK_PING_INTERVAL;
70}

72rtc::AdapterType GuessAdapterTypeFromNetworkCost(int network_cost) {
73 // The current network costs have been unchanged since they were added
74 // to webrtc. If they ever were to change we would need to reconsider
75 // this method.
76 switch (network_cost) {
77 case rtc::kNetworkCostMin:
78 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_ETHERNET;
79 case rtc::kNetworkCostLow:
80 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_WIFI;
81 case rtc::kNetworkCostCellular:
82 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR;
83 case rtc::kNetworkCostCellular2G:
84 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_2G;
85 case rtc::kNetworkCostCellular3G:
86 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_3G;
87 case rtc::kNetworkCostCellular4G:
88 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_4G;
89 case rtc::kNetworkCostCellular5G:
90 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_5G;
91 case rtc::kNetworkCostUnknown:
92 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_UNKNOWN;
93 case rtc::kNetworkCostMax:
94 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_ANY;
95 }
96 return rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_UNKNOWN;
97}
98
99rtc::RouteEndpoint CreateRouteEndpointFromCandidate(
100 bool local,
101 const cricket::Candidate& candidate,
102 bool uses_turn) {
103 auto adapter_type = candidate.network_type();
104 if (!local && adapter_type == rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_UNKNOWN) {
105 adapter_type = GuessAdapterTypeFromNetworkCost(candidate.network_cost());
106 }
107
108 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/9446) : Rewrite if information about remote network
109 // adapter becomes available. The implication of this implementation is that
110 // we will only ever report 1 adapter per type. In practice this is probably
111 // fine, since the endpoint also contains network-id.
112 uint16_t adapter_id = static_cast<int>(adapter_type);
113 return rtc::RouteEndpoint(adapter_type, adapter_id, candidate.network_id(),
114 uses_turn);
115}

125bool IceCredentialsChanged(const std::string& old_ufrag,
126 const std::string& old_pwd,
127 const std::string& new_ufrag,
128 const std::string& new_pwd) {
129 // The standard (RFC 5245 Section 9.1.1.1) says that ICE restarts MUST change
130 // both the ufrag and password. However, section 9.2.1.1 says changing the
131 // ufrag OR password indicates an ICE restart. So, to keep compatibility with
132 // endpoints that only change one, we'll treat this as an ICE restart.
133 return (old_ufrag != new_ufrag) || (old_pwd != new_pwd);
134}

161// Private constructor, called from Create()
162P2PTransportChannel::P2PTransportChannel(
163 const std::string& transport_name,
164 int component,
165 PortAllocator* allocator,
166 webrtc::AsyncDnsResolverFactoryInterface* async_dns_resolver_factory,
167 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AsyncDnsResolverFactoryInterface>
168 owned_dns_resolver_factory,
169 webrtc::RtcEventLog* event_log,
170 IceControllerFactoryInterface* ice_controller_factory)
171 : transport_name_(transport_name),
172 component_(component),
173 allocator_(allocator),
174 // If owned_dns_resolver_factory is given, async_dns_resolver_factory is
175 // ignored.
176 async_dns_resolver_factory_(owned_dns_resolver_factory
177 ? owned_dns_resolver_factory.get()
178 : async_dns_resolver_factory),
179 owned_dns_resolver_factory_(std::move(owned_dns_resolver_factory)),
180 network_thread_(rtc::Thread::Current()),
181 incoming_only_(false),
182 error_(0),
183 sort_dirty_(false),
184 remote_ice_mode_(ICEMODE_FULL),
185 ice_role_(ICEROLE_UNKNOWN),
186 tiebreaker_(0),
187 gathering_state_(kIceGatheringNew),
188 config_(RECEIVING_TIMEOUT,
189 BACKUP_CONNECTION_PING_INTERVAL,
190 GATHER_ONCE /* continual_gathering_policy */,
191 false /* prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs */,
192 STRONG_AND_STABLE_WRITABLE_CONNECTION_PING_INTERVAL,
193 true /* presume_writable_when_fully_relayed */,
194 REGATHER_ON_FAILED_NETWORKS_INTERVAL,
195 RECEIVING_SWITCHING_DELAY) {
196 RTC_DCHECK(allocator_ != nullptr);
197 weak_ping_interval_ = GetWeakPingIntervalInFieldTrial();
198 // Validate IceConfig even for mostly built-in constant default values in case
199 // we change them.
200 RTC_DCHECK(ValidateIceConfig(config_).ok());
201 webrtc::BasicRegatheringController::Config regathering_config;
202 regathering_config.regather_on_failed_networks_interval =
203 config_.regather_on_failed_networks_interval_or_default();
204 regathering_controller_ =
205 std::make_unique<webrtc::BasicRegatheringController>(
206 regathering_config, this, network_thread_);
207 // We populate the change in the candidate filter to the session taken by
208 // the transport.
209 allocator_->SignalCandidateFilterChanged.connect(
210 this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidateFilterChanged);
211 ice_event_log_.set_event_log(event_log);
212
213 IceControllerFactoryArgs args{
214 [this] { return GetState(); }, [this] { return GetIceRole(); },
215 [this](const Connection* connection) {
216 // TODO(webrtc:10647/jonaso): Figure out a way to remove friendship
217 // between P2PTransportChannel and Connection.
218 return IsPortPruned(connection->port()) ||
219 IsRemoteCandidatePruned(connection->remote_candidate());
220 },
221 &field_trials_,
222 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-IceControllerFieldTrials")};
223 if (ice_controller_factory != nullptr) {
224 ice_controller_ = ice_controller_factory->Create(args);
225 } else {
226 ice_controller_ = std::make_unique<BasicIceController>(args);
227 }
228}

249P2PTransportChannel::~P2PTransportChannel() {
250 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
251 std::vector<Connection*> copy(connections().begin(), connections().end());
252 for (Connection* con : copy) {
253 con->Destroy();
254 }
255 resolvers_.clear();
256}

258// Add the allocator session to our list so that we know which sessions
259// are still active.
260void P2PTransportChannel::AddAllocatorSession(
261 std::unique_ptr<PortAllocatorSession> session) {
262 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
263
264 session->set_generation(static_cast<uint32_t>(allocator_sessions_.size()));
265 session->SignalPortReady.connect(this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnPortReady);
266 session->SignalPortsPruned.connect(this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnPortsPruned);
267 session->SignalCandidatesReady.connect(
268 this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidatesReady);
269 session->SignalCandidateError.connect(this,
270 &P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidateError);
271 session->SignalCandidatesRemoved.connect(
272 this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidatesRemoved);
273 session->SignalCandidatesAllocationDone.connect(
274 this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidatesAllocationDone);
275 if (!allocator_sessions_.empty()) {
276 allocator_session()->PruneAllPorts();
277 }
278 allocator_sessions_.push_back(std::move(session));
279 regathering_controller_->set_allocator_session(allocator_session());
280
281 // We now only want to apply new candidates that we receive to the ports
282 // created by this new session because these are replacing those of the
283 // previous sessions.
284 PruneAllPorts();
285}

287void P2PTransportChannel::AddConnection(Connection* connection) {
288 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
289 connection->set_remote_ice_mode(remote_ice_mode_);
290 connection->set_receiving_timeout(config_.receiving_timeout);
291 connection->set_unwritable_timeout(config_.ice_unwritable_timeout);
292 connection->set_unwritable_min_checks(config_.ice_unwritable_min_checks);
293 connection->set_inactive_timeout(config_.ice_inactive_timeout);
294 connection->SignalReadPacket.connect(this,
295 &P2PTransportChannel::OnReadPacket);
296 connection->SignalReadyToSend.connect(this,
297 &P2PTransportChannel::OnReadyToSend);
298 connection->SignalStateChange.connect(
299 this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnConnectionStateChange);
300 connection->SignalDestroyed.connect(
301 this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnConnectionDestroyed);
302 connection->SignalNominated.connect(this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnNominated);
303
304 had_connection_ = true;
305
306 connection->set_ice_event_log(&ice_event_log_);
307 connection->SetIceFieldTrials(&field_trials_);
308 LogCandidatePairConfig(connection,
309 webrtc::IceCandidatePairConfigType::kAdded);
310
311 ice_controller_->AddConnection(connection);
312}

314bool P2PTransportChannel::MaybeSwitchSelectedConnection(
315 Connection* new_connection,
316 IceControllerEvent reason) {
317 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
318
319 return MaybeSwitchSelectedConnection(
320 reason, ice_controller_->ShouldSwitchConnection(reason, new_connection));
321}
322
323bool P2PTransportChannel::MaybeSwitchSelectedConnection(
324 IceControllerEvent reason,
325 IceControllerInterface::SwitchResult result) {
326 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
327 if (result.connection.has_value()) {
328 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Switching selected connection due to: "
329 << reason.ToString();
330 SwitchSelectedConnection(FromIceController(*result.connection), reason);
331 }
332
333 if (result.recheck_event.has_value()) {
334 // If we do not switch to the connection because it missed the receiving
335 // threshold, the new connection is in a better receiving state than the
336 // currently selected connection. So we need to re-check whether it needs
337 // to be switched at a later time.
338 network_thread_->PostDelayedTask(
339 ToQueuedTask(task_safety_,
340 [this, recheck = *result.recheck_event]() {
341 SortConnectionsAndUpdateState(recheck);
342 }),
343 result.recheck_event->recheck_delay_ms);
344 }
345
346 for (const auto* con : result.connections_to_forget_state_on) {
347 FromIceController(con)->ForgetLearnedState();
348 }
349
350 return result.connection.has_value();
351}

353void P2PTransportChannel::SetIceRole(IceRole ice_role) {
354 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
355 if (ice_role_ != ice_role) {
356 ice_role_ = ice_role;
357 for (PortInterface* port : ports_) {
358 port->SetIceRole(ice_role);
359 }
360 // Update role on pruned ports as well, because they may still have
361 // connections alive that should be using the correct role.
362 for (PortInterface* port : pruned_ports_) {
363 port->SetIceRole(ice_role);
364 }
365 }
366}

429absl::optional<const CandidatePair>
430P2PTransportChannel::GetSelectedCandidatePair() const {
431 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
432 if (selected_connection_ == nullptr) {
433 return absl::nullopt;
434 }
435
436 CandidatePair pair;
437 pair.local = SanitizeLocalCandidate(selected_connection_->local_candidate());
438 pair.remote =
439 SanitizeRemoteCandidate(selected_connection_->remote_candidate());
440 return pair;
441}

443// A channel is considered ICE completed once there is at most one active
444// connection per network and at least one active connection.
445IceTransportState P2PTransportChannel::ComputeState() const {
446 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
447 if (!had_connection_) {
448 return IceTransportState::STATE_INIT;
449 }
450
451 std::vector<Connection*> active_connections;
452 for (Connection* connection : connections()) {
453 if (connection->active()) {
454 active_connections.push_back(connection);
455 }
456 }
457 if (active_connections.empty()) {
458 return IceTransportState::STATE_FAILED;
459 }
460
461 std::set<const rtc::Network*> networks;
462 for (Connection* connection : active_connections) {
463 const rtc::Network* network = connection->network();
464 if (networks.find(network) == networks.end()) {
465 networks.insert(network);
466 } else {
467 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString()
468 << ": Ice not completed yet for this channel as "
469 << network->ToString()
470 << " has more than 1 connection.";
471 return IceTransportState::STATE_CONNECTING;
472 }
473 }
474
475 ice_event_log_.DumpCandidatePairDescriptionToMemoryAsConfigEvents();
476 return IceTransportState::STATE_COMPLETED;
477}
478
479// Compute the current RTCIceTransportState as described in
480// https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/#dom-rtcicetransportstate
481// TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/9218): Start signaling kCompleted once we have
482// implemented end-of-candidates signalling.
483webrtc::IceTransportState P2PTransportChannel::ComputeIceTransportState()
484 const {
485 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
486 bool has_connection = false;
487 for (Connection* connection : connections()) {
488 if (connection->active()) {
489 has_connection = true;
490 break;
491 }
492 }
493
494 if (had_connection_ && !has_connection) {
495 return webrtc::IceTransportState::kFailed;
496 }
497
498 if (!writable() && has_been_writable_) {
499 return webrtc::IceTransportState::kDisconnected;
500 }
501
502 if (!had_connection_ && !has_connection) {
503 return webrtc::IceTransportState::kNew;
504 }
505
506 if (has_connection && !writable()) {
507 // A candidate pair has been formed by adding a remote candidate
508 // and gathering a local candidate.
509 return webrtc::IceTransportState::kChecking;
510 }
511
512 return webrtc::IceTransportState::kConnected;
513}

515void P2PTransportChannel::SetIceParameters(const IceParameters& ice_params) {
516 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
517 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Set ICE ufrag: " << ice_params.ufrag
518 << " pwd: " << ice_params.pwd << " on transport "
519 << transport_name();
520 ice_parameters_ = ice_params;
521 // Note: Candidate gathering will restart when MaybeStartGathering is next
522 // called.
523}
524
525void P2PTransportChannel::SetRemoteIceParameters(
526 const IceParameters& ice_params) {
527 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
528 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Received remote ICE parameters: ufrag="
529 << ice_params.ufrag << ", renomination "
530 << (ice_params.renomination ? "enabled" : "disabled");
531 IceParameters* current_ice = remote_ice();
532 if (!current_ice || *current_ice != ice_params) {
533 // Keep the ICE credentials so that newer connections
534 // are prioritized over the older ones.
535 remote_ice_parameters_.push_back(ice_params);
536 }
537
538 // Update the pwd of remote candidate if needed.
539 for (RemoteCandidate& candidate : remote_candidates_) {
540 if (candidate.username() == ice_params.ufrag &&
541 candidate.password().empty()) {
542 candidate.set_password(ice_params.pwd);
543 }
544 }
545 // We need to update the credentials and generation for any peer reflexive
546 // candidates.
547 for (Connection* conn : connections()) {
548 conn->MaybeSetRemoteIceParametersAndGeneration(
549 ice_params, static_cast<int>(remote_ice_parameters_.size() - 1));
550 }
551 // Updating the remote ICE candidate generation could change the sort order.
552 RequestSortAndStateUpdate(
553 IceControllerEvent::REMOTE_CANDIDATE_GENERATION_CHANGE);
554}

561// TODO(qingsi): We apply the convention that setting a absl::optional parameter
562// to null restores its default value in the implementation. However, some
563// absl::optional parameters are only processed below if non-null, e.g.,
564// regather_on_failed_networks_interval, and thus there is no way to restore the
565// defaults. Fix this issue later for consistency.
566void P2PTransportChannel::SetIceConfig(const IceConfig& config) {
567 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
568 if (config_.continual_gathering_policy != config.continual_gathering_policy) {
569 if (!allocator_sessions_.empty()) {
570 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Trying to change continual gathering policy "
571 "when gathering has already started!";
572 } else {
573 config_.continual_gathering_policy = config.continual_gathering_policy;
574 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Set continual_gathering_policy to "
575 << config_.continual_gathering_policy;
576 }
577 }
578
579 if (config_.backup_connection_ping_interval !=
580 config.backup_connection_ping_interval) {
581 config_.backup_connection_ping_interval =
582 config.backup_connection_ping_interval;
583 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Set backup connection ping interval to "
584 << config_.backup_connection_ping_interval_or_default()
585 << " milliseconds.";
586 }
587 if (config_.receiving_timeout != config.receiving_timeout) {
588 config_.receiving_timeout = config.receiving_timeout;
589 for (Connection* connection : connections()) {
590 connection->set_receiving_timeout(config_.receiving_timeout);
591 }
592 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Set ICE receiving timeout to "
593 << config_.receiving_timeout_or_default()
594 << " milliseconds";
595 }
596
597 config_.prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs =
598 config.prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs;
599 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Set ping most likely connection to "
600 << config_.prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs;
601
602 if (config_.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval !=
603 config.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval) {
604 config_.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval =
605 config.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval;
606 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
607 << "Set stable_writable_connection_ping_interval to "
608 << config_.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_or_default();
609 }
610
611 if (config_.presume_writable_when_fully_relayed !=
612 config.presume_writable_when_fully_relayed) {
613 if (!connections().empty()) {
614 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Trying to change 'presume writable' "
615 "while connections already exist!";
616 } else {
617 config_.presume_writable_when_fully_relayed =
618 config.presume_writable_when_fully_relayed;
619 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Set presume writable when fully relayed to "
620 << config_.presume_writable_when_fully_relayed;
621 }
622 }
623
624 config_.surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed =
625 config.surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed;
626 if (config_.surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed &&
627 config_.continual_gathering_policy != GATHER_CONTINUALLY) {
628 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
629 << "surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed is "
630 "ineffective since we do not gather continually.";
631 }
632
633 if (config_.regather_on_failed_networks_interval !=
634 config.regather_on_failed_networks_interval) {
635 config_.regather_on_failed_networks_interval =
636 config.regather_on_failed_networks_interval;
637 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
638 << "Set regather_on_failed_networks_interval to "
639 << config_.regather_on_failed_networks_interval_or_default();
640 }
641
642 if (config_.receiving_switching_delay != config.receiving_switching_delay) {
643 config_.receiving_switching_delay = config.receiving_switching_delay;
644 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Set receiving_switching_delay to "
645 << config_.receiving_switching_delay_or_default();
646 }
647
648 if (config_.default_nomination_mode != config.default_nomination_mode) {

806// TODO(qingsi): Add tests for the config validation starting from
807// PeerConnection::SetConfiguration.
808// Static
809RTCError P2PTransportChannel::ValidateIceConfig(const IceConfig& config) {
810 if (config.ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity_or_default() <
811 config.ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity.value_or(
812 GetWeakPingIntervalInFieldTrial())) {
813 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
814 "Ping interval of candidate pairs is shorter when ICE is "
815 "strongly connected than that when ICE is weakly "
816 "connected");
817 }
818
819 if (config.receiving_timeout_or_default() <
820 std::max(config.ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity_or_default(),
821 config.ice_check_min_interval_or_default())) {
822 return RTCError(
823 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
824 "Receiving timeout is shorter than the minimal ping interval.");
825 }
826
827 if (config.backup_connection_ping_interval_or_default() <
828 config.ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity_or_default()) {
829 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
830 "Ping interval of backup candidate pairs is shorter than "
831 "that of general candidate pairs when ICE is strongly "
832 "connected");
833 }
834
835 if (config.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_or_default() <
836 config.ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity_or_default()) {
837 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
838 "Ping interval of stable and writable candidate pairs is "
839 "shorter than that of general candidate pairs when ICE is "
840 "strongly connected");
841 }
842
843 if (config.ice_unwritable_timeout_or_default() >
844 config.ice_inactive_timeout_or_default()) {
845 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
846 "The timeout period for the writability state to become "
847 "UNRELIABLE is longer than that to become TIMEOUT.");
848 }
849
850 return RTCError::OK();
851}

864void P2PTransportChannel::MaybeStartGathering() {
865 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
866 if (ice_parameters_.ufrag.empty() || ice_parameters_.pwd.empty()) {
867 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
868 << "Cannot gather candidates because ICE parameters are empty"
869 " ufrag: "
870 << ice_parameters_.ufrag << " pwd: " << ice_parameters_.pwd;
871 return;
872 }
873 // Start gathering if we never started before, or if an ICE restart occurred.
874 if (allocator_sessions_.empty() ||
875 IceCredentialsChanged(allocator_sessions_.back()->ice_ufrag(),
876 allocator_sessions_.back()->ice_pwd(),
877 ice_parameters_.ufrag, ice_parameters_.pwd)) {
878 if (gathering_state_ != kIceGatheringGathering) {
879 gathering_state_ = kIceGatheringGathering;
880 SignalGatheringState(this);
881 }
882
883 if (!allocator_sessions_.empty()) {
884 IceRestartState state;
885 if (writable()) {
886 state = IceRestartState::CONNECTED;
887 } else if (IsGettingPorts()) {
888 state = IceRestartState::CONNECTING;
889 } else {
890 state = IceRestartState::DISCONNECTED;
891 }
892 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.IceRestartState",
893 static_cast<int>(state),
894 static_cast<int>(IceRestartState::MAX_VALUE));
895 }
896
897 for (const auto& session : allocator_sessions_) {
898 if (session->IsStopped()) {
899 continue;
900 }
901 session->StopGettingPorts();
902 }
903
904 // Time for a new allocator.
905 std::unique_ptr<PortAllocatorSession> pooled_session =
906 allocator_->TakePooledSession(transport_name(), component(),
907 ice_parameters_.ufrag,
908 ice_parameters_.pwd);
909 if (pooled_session) {
910 AddAllocatorSession(std::move(pooled_session));
911 PortAllocatorSession* raw_pooled_session =
912 allocator_sessions_.back().get();
913 // Process the pooled session's existing candidates/ports, if they exist.
914 OnCandidatesReady(raw_pooled_session,
915 raw_pooled_session->ReadyCandidates());
916 for (PortInterface* port : allocator_sessions_.back()->ReadyPorts()) {
917 OnPortReady(raw_pooled_session, port);
918 }
919 if (allocator_sessions_.back()->CandidatesAllocationDone()) {
920 OnCandidatesAllocationDone(raw_pooled_session);
921 }
922 } else {
923 AddAllocatorSession(allocator_->CreateSession(
924 transport_name(), component(), ice_parameters_.ufrag,
925 ice_parameters_.pwd));
926 allocator_sessions_.back()->StartGettingPorts();
927 }
928 }
929}
930
931// A new port is available, attempt to make connections for it
932void P2PTransportChannel::OnPortReady(PortAllocatorSession* session,
933 PortInterface* port) {
934 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
935
936 // Set in-effect options on the new port
937 for (OptionMap::const_iterator it = options_.begin(); it != options_.end();
938 ++it) {
939 int val = port->SetOption(it->first, it->second);
940 if (val < 0) {
941 // Errors are frequent, so use LS_INFO. bugs.webrtc.org/9221
942 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << port->ToString() << ": SetOption(" << it->first
943 << ", " << it->second
944 << ") failed: " << port->GetError();
945 }
946 }
947
948 // Remember the ports and candidates, and signal that candidates are ready.
949 // The session will handle this, and send an initiate/accept/modify message
950 // if one is pending.
951
952 port->SetIceRole(ice_role_);
953 port->SetIceTiebreaker(tiebreaker_);
954 ports_.push_back(port);
955 port->SignalUnknownAddress.connect(this,
956 &P2PTransportChannel::OnUnknownAddress);
957 port->SubscribePortDestroyed(
958 [this](PortInterface* port) { OnPortDestroyed(port); });
959
960 port->SignalRoleConflict.connect(this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnRoleConflict);
961 port->SignalSentPacket.connect(this, &P2PTransportChannel::OnSentPacket);
962
963 // Attempt to create a connection from this new port to all of the remote
964 // candidates that we were given so far.
965
966 std::vector<RemoteCandidate>::iterator iter;
967 for (iter = remote_candidates_.begin(); iter != remote_candidates_.end();
968 ++iter) {
969 CreateConnection(port, *iter, iter->origin_port());
970 }
971
972 SortConnectionsAndUpdateState(
973 IceControllerEvent::NEW_CONNECTION_FROM_LOCAL_CANDIDATE);
974}
975
976// A new candidate is available, let listeners know
977void P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidatesReady(
978 PortAllocatorSession* session,
979 const std::vector<Candidate>& candidates) {
980 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
981 for (size_t i = 0; i < candidates.size(); ++i) {
982 SignalCandidateGathered(this, candidates[i]);
983 }
984}

986void P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidateError(
987 PortAllocatorSession* session,
988 const IceCandidateErrorEvent& event) {
989 RTC_DCHECK(network_thread_ == rtc::Thread::Current());
990 SignalCandidateError(this, event);
991}

993void P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidatesAllocationDone(
994 PortAllocatorSession* session) {
995 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
996 if (config_.gather_continually()) {
997 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "P2PTransportChannel: " << transport_name()
998 << ", component " << component()
999 << " gathering complete, but using continual "
1000 "gathering so not changing gathering state.";
1001 return;
1002 }
1003 gathering_state_ = kIceGatheringComplete;
1004 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "P2PTransportChannel: " << transport_name()
1005 << ", component " << component() << " gathering complete";
1006 SignalGatheringState(this);
1007}

1009// Handle stun packets
1010void P2PTransportChannel::OnUnknownAddress(PortInterface* port,
1011 const rtc::SocketAddress& address,
1012 ProtocolType proto,
1013 IceMessage* stun_msg,
1014 const std::string& remote_username,
1015 bool port_muxed) {
1016 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1017
1018 // Port has received a valid stun packet from an address that no Connection
1019 // is currently available for. See if we already have a candidate with the
1020 // address. If it isn't we need to create new candidate for it.
1021 //
1022 // TODO(qingsi): There is a caveat of the logic below if we have remote
1023 // candidates with hostnames. We could create a prflx candidate that is
1024 // identical to a host candidate that are currently in the process of name
1025 // resolution. We would not have a duplicate candidate since when adding the
1026 // resolved host candidate, FinishingAddingRemoteCandidate does
1027 // MaybeUpdatePeerReflexiveCandidate, and the prflx candidate would be updated
1028 // to a host candidate. As a result, for a brief moment we would have a prflx
1029 // candidate showing a private IP address, though we do not signal prflx
1030 // candidates to applications and we could obfuscate the IP addresses of prflx
1031 // candidates in P2PTransportChannel::GetStats. The difficulty of preventing
1032 // creating the prflx from the beginning is that we do not have a reliable way
1033 // to claim two candidates are identical without the address information. If
1034 // we always pause the addition of a prflx candidate when there is ongoing
1035 // name resolution and dedup after we have a resolved address, we run into the
1036 // risk of losing/delaying the addition of a non-identical candidate that
1037 // could be the only way to have a connection, if the resolution never
1038 // completes or is significantly delayed.
1039 const Candidate* candidate = nullptr;
1040 for (const Candidate& c : remote_candidates_) {
1041 if (c.username() == remote_username && c.address() == address &&
1042 c.protocol() == ProtoToString(proto)) {
1043 candidate = &c;
1044 break;
1045 }
1046 }
1047
1048 uint32_t remote_generation = 0;
1049 std::string remote_password;
1050 // The STUN binding request may arrive after setRemoteDescription and before
1051 // adding remote candidate, so we need to set the password to the shared
1052 // password and set the generation if the user name matches.
1053 const IceParameters* ice_param =
1054 FindRemoteIceFromUfrag(remote_username, &remote_generation);
1055 // Note: if not found, the remote_generation will still be 0.
1056 if (ice_param != nullptr) {
1057 remote_password = ice_param->pwd;
1058 }
1059
1060 Candidate remote_candidate;
1061 bool remote_candidate_is_new = (candidate == nullptr);
1062 if (!remote_candidate_is_new) {
1063 remote_candidate = *candidate;
1064 } else {
1065 // Create a new candidate with this address.
1066 // The priority of the candidate is set to the PRIORITY attribute
1067 // from the request.
1068 const StunUInt32Attribute* priority_attr =
1069 stun_msg->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_PRIORITY);
1070 if (!priority_attr) {
1071 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "P2PTransportChannel::OnUnknownAddress - "
1072 "No STUN_ATTR_PRIORITY found in the "
1073 "stun request message";
1074 port->SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg, address, STUN_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST,
1075 STUN_ERROR_REASON_BAD_REQUEST);
1076 return;
1077 }
1078 int remote_candidate_priority = priority_attr->value();
1079
1080 uint16_t network_id = 0;
1081 uint16_t network_cost = 0;
1082 const StunUInt32Attribute* network_attr =
1083 stun_msg->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_GOOG_NETWORK_INFO);
1084 if (network_attr) {
1085 uint32_t network_info = network_attr->value();
1086 network_id = static_cast<uint16_t>(network_info >> 16);
1087 network_cost = static_cast<uint16_t>(network_info);
1088 }
1089
1090 // RFC 5245
1091 // If the source transport address of the request does not match any
1092 // existing remote candidates, it represents a new peer reflexive remote
1093 // candidate.
1094 remote_candidate = Candidate(
1095 component(), ProtoToString(proto), address, remote_candidate_priority,
1096 remote_username, remote_password, PRFLX_PORT_TYPE, remote_generation,
1097 "", network_id, network_cost);
1098 if (proto == PROTO_TCP) {
1099 remote_candidate.set_tcptype(TCPTYPE_ACTIVE_STR);
1100 }
1101
1102 // From RFC 5245, section-7.2.1.3:
1103 // The foundation of the candidate is set to an arbitrary value, different
1104 // from the foundation for all other remote candidates.
1105 remote_candidate.set_foundation(
1106 rtc::ToString(rtc::ComputeCrc32(remote_candidate.id())));
1107 }
1108
1109 // RFC5245, the agent constructs a pair whose local candidate is equal to
1110 // the transport address on which the STUN request was received, and a
1111 // remote candidate equal to the source transport address where the
1112 // request came from.
1113
1114 // There shouldn't be an existing connection with this remote address.
1115 // When ports are muxed, this channel might get multiple unknown address
1116 // signals. In that case if the connection is already exists, we should
1117 // simply ignore the signal otherwise send server error.
1118 if (port->GetConnection(remote_candidate.address())) {
1119 if (port_muxed) {
1120 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Connection already exists for peer reflexive "
1121 "candidate: "
1122 << remote_candidate.ToSensitiveString();
1123 return;
1124 } else {
1125 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1126 port->SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg, address, STUN_ERROR_SERVER_ERROR,
1127 STUN_ERROR_REASON_SERVER_ERROR);
1128 return;
1129 }
1130 }
1131
1132 Connection* connection =
1133 port->CreateConnection(remote_candidate, PortInterface::ORIGIN_THIS_PORT);
1134 if (!connection) {
1135 // This could happen in some scenarios. For example, a TurnPort may have
1136 // had a refresh request timeout, so it won't create connections.
1137 port->SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg, address, STUN_ERROR_SERVER_ERROR,
1138 STUN_ERROR_REASON_SERVER_ERROR);
1139 return;
1140 }
1141
1142 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Adding connection from "
1143 << (remote_candidate_is_new ? "peer reflexive"
1144 : "resurrected")
1145 << " candidate: " << remote_candidate.ToSensitiveString();
1146 AddConnection(connection);
1147 connection->HandleStunBindingOrGoogPingRequest(stun_msg);
1148
1149 // Update the list of connections since we just added another. We do this
1150 // after sending the response since it could (in principle) delete the
1151 // connection in question.
1152 SortConnectionsAndUpdateState(
1153 IceControllerEvent::NEW_CONNECTION_FROM_UNKNOWN_REMOTE_ADDRESS);
1154}

1171
1172const IceParameters* P2PTransportChannel::FindRemoteIceFromUfrag(
1173 const std::string& ufrag,
1174 uint32_t* generation) {
1175 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1176 const auto& params = remote_ice_parameters_;
1177 auto it = std::find_if(
1178 params.rbegin(), params.rend(),
1179 [ufrag](const IceParameters& param) { return param.ufrag == ufrag; });
1180 if (it == params.rend()) {
1181 // Not found.
1182 return nullptr;
1183 }
1184 *generation = params.rend() - it - 1;
1185 return &(*it);
1186}
1187
1188void P2PTransportChannel::OnNominated(Connection* conn) {
1189 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1190 RTC_DCHECK(ice_role_ == ICEROLE_CONTROLLED);
1191
1192 if (selected_connection_ == conn) {
1193 return;
1194 }
1195
1196 if (field_trials_.send_ping_on_nomination_ice_controlled && conn != nullptr) {
1197 PingConnection(conn);
1198 MarkConnectionPinged(conn);
1199 }
1200
1201 // TODO(qingsi): RequestSortAndStateUpdate will eventually call
1202 // MaybeSwitchSelectedConnection again. Rewrite this logic.
1203 if (MaybeSwitchSelectedConnection(
1204 conn, IceControllerEvent::NOMINATION_ON_CONTROLLED_SIDE)) {
1205 // Now that we have selected a connection, it is time to prune other
1206 // connections and update the read/write state of the channel.
1207 RequestSortAndStateUpdate(
1208 IceControllerEvent::NOMINATION_ON_CONTROLLED_SIDE);
1209 } else {
1210 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
1211 << "Not switching the selected connection on controlled side yet: "
1212 << conn->ToString();
1213 }
1214}

1216void P2PTransportChannel::ResolveHostnameCandidate(const Candidate& candidate) {
1217 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1218 if (!async_dns_resolver_factory_) {
1219 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Dropping ICE candidate with hostname address "
1220 "(no AsyncResolverFactory)";
1221 return;
1222 }
1223
1224 auto resolver = async_dns_resolver_factory_->Create();
1225 auto resptr = resolver.get();
1226 resolvers_.emplace_back(candidate, std::move(resolver));
1227 resptr->Start(candidate.address(),
1228 [this, resptr]() { OnCandidateResolved(resptr); });
1229 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Asynchronously resolving ICE candidate hostname "
1230 << candidate.address().HostAsSensitiveURIString();
1231}
1232
1233void P2PTransportChannel::AddRemoteCandidate(const Candidate& candidate) {
1234 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1235
1236 uint32_t generation = GetRemoteCandidateGeneration(candidate);
1237 // If a remote candidate with a previous generation arrives, drop it.
1238 if (generation < remote_ice_generation()) {
1239 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Dropping a remote candidate because its ufrag "
1240 << candidate.username()
1241 << " indicates it was for a previous generation.";
1242 return;
1243 }
1244
1245 Candidate new_remote_candidate(candidate);
1246 new_remote_candidate.set_generation(generation);
1247 // ICE candidates don't need to have username and password set, but
1248 // the code below this (specifically, ConnectionRequest::Prepare in
1249 // port.cc) uses the remote candidates's username. So, we set it
1250 // here.
1251 if (remote_ice()) {
1252 if (candidate.username().empty()) {
1253 new_remote_candidate.set_username(remote_ice()->ufrag);
1254 }
1255 if (new_remote_candidate.username() == remote_ice()->ufrag) {
1256 if (candidate.password().empty()) {
1257 new_remote_candidate.set_password(remote_ice()->pwd);
1258 }
1259 } else {
1260 // The candidate belongs to the next generation. Its pwd will be set
1261 // when the new remote ICE credentials arrive.
1262 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1263 << "A remote candidate arrives with an unknown ufrag: "
1264 << candidate.username();
1265 }
1266 }
1267
1268 if (new_remote_candidate.address().IsUnresolvedIP()) {
1269 // Don't do DNS lookups if the IceTransportPolicy is "none" or "relay".
1270 bool sharing_host = ((allocator_->candidate_filter() & CF_HOST) != 0);
1271 bool sharing_stun = ((allocator_->candidate_filter() & CF_REFLEXIVE) != 0);
1272 if (sharing_host || sharing_stun) {
1273 ResolveHostnameCandidate(new_remote_candidate);
1274 }
1275 return;
1276 }
1277
1278 FinishAddingRemoteCandidate(new_remote_candidate);
1279}
1280
1281P2PTransportChannel::CandidateAndResolver::CandidateAndResolver(
1282 const Candidate& candidate,
1283 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AsyncDnsResolverInterface>&& resolver)
1284 : candidate_(candidate), resolver_(std::move(resolver)) {}
1285
1286P2PTransportChannel::CandidateAndResolver::~CandidateAndResolver() {}
1287
1288void P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidateResolved(
1289 webrtc::AsyncDnsResolverInterface* resolver) {
1290 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1291 auto p =
1292 absl::c_find_if(resolvers_, [resolver](const CandidateAndResolver& cr) {
1293 return cr.resolver_.get() == resolver;
1294 });
1295 if (p == resolvers_.end()) {
1296 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Unexpected AsyncDnsResolver return";
1297 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1298 return;
1299 }
1300 Candidate candidate = p->candidate_;
1301 AddRemoteCandidateWithResult(candidate, resolver->result());
1302 // Now we can delete the resolver.
1303 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/12651): Replace the stuff below with
1304 // resolvers_.erase(p);
1305 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AsyncDnsResolverInterface> to_delete =
1306 std::move(p->resolver_);
1307 // Delay the actual deletion of the resolver until the lambda executes.
1308 network_thread_->PostTask(
1309 ToQueuedTask([delete_this = std::move(to_delete)] {}));
1310 resolvers_.erase(p);
1311}
1312
1313void P2PTransportChannel::AddRemoteCandidateWithResult(
1314 Candidate candidate,
1315 const webrtc::AsyncDnsResolverResult& result) {
1316 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1317 if (result.GetError()) {
1318 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to resolve ICE candidate hostname "
1319 << candidate.address().HostAsSensitiveURIString()
1320 << " with error " << result.GetError();
1321 return;
1322 }
1323
1324 rtc::SocketAddress resolved_address;
1325 // Prefer IPv6 to IPv4 if we have it (see RFC 5245 Section 15.1).
1326 // TODO(zstein): This won't work if we only have IPv4 locally but receive an
1327 // AAAA DNS record.
1328 bool have_address = result.GetResolvedAddress(AF_INET6, &resolved_address) ||
1329 result.GetResolvedAddress(AF_INET, &resolved_address);
1330 if (!have_address) {
1331 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "ICE candidate hostname "
1332 << candidate.address().HostAsSensitiveURIString()
1333 << " could not be resolved";
1334 return;
1335 }
1336
1337 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Resolved ICE candidate hostname "
1338 << candidate.address().HostAsSensitiveURIString() << " to "
1339 << resolved_address.ipaddr().ToSensitiveString();
1340 candidate.set_address(resolved_address);
1341 FinishAddingRemoteCandidate(candidate);
1342}
1343
1344void P2PTransportChannel::FinishAddingRemoteCandidate(
1345 const Candidate& new_remote_candidate) {
1346 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1347 // If this candidate matches what was thought to be a peer reflexive
1348 // candidate, we need to update the candidate priority/etc.
1349 for (Connection* conn : connections()) {
1350 conn->MaybeUpdatePeerReflexiveCandidate(new_remote_candidate);
1351 }
1352
1353 // Create connections to this remote candidate.
1354 CreateConnections(new_remote_candidate, NULL);
1355
1356 // Resort the connections list, which may have new elements.
1357 SortConnectionsAndUpdateState(
1358 IceControllerEvent::NEW_CONNECTION_FROM_REMOTE_CANDIDATE);
1359}
1360
1361void P2PTransportChannel::RemoveRemoteCandidate(
1362 const Candidate& cand_to_remove) {
1363 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1364 auto iter =
1365 std::remove_if(remote_candidates_.begin(), remote_candidates_.end(),
1366 [cand_to_remove](const Candidate& candidate) {
1367 return cand_to_remove.MatchesForRemoval(candidate);
1368 });
1369 if (iter != remote_candidates_.end()) {
1370 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Removed remote candidate "
1371 << cand_to_remove.ToSensitiveString();
1372 remote_candidates_.erase(iter, remote_candidates_.end());
1373 }
1374}
1375
1376void P2PTransportChannel::RemoveAllRemoteCandidates() {
1377 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1378 remote_candidates_.clear();
1379}
1380
1381// Creates connections from all of the ports that we care about to the given
1382// remote candidate. The return value is true if we created a connection from
1383// the origin port.
1384bool P2PTransportChannel::CreateConnections(const Candidate& remote_candidate,
1385 PortInterface* origin_port) {
1386 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1387
1388 // If we've already seen the new remote candidate (in the current candidate
1389 // generation), then we shouldn't try creating connections for it.
1390 // We either already have a connection for it, or we previously created one
1391 // and then later pruned it. If we don't return, the channel will again
1392 // re-create any connections that were previously pruned, which will then
1393 // immediately be re-pruned, churning the network for no purpose.
1394 // This only applies to candidates received over signaling (i.e. origin_port
1395 // is NULL).
1396 if (!origin_port && IsDuplicateRemoteCandidate(remote_candidate)) {
1397 // return true to indicate success, without creating any new connections.
1398 return true;
1399 }
1400
1401 // Add a new connection for this candidate to every port that allows such a
1402 // connection (i.e., if they have compatible protocols) and that does not
1403 // already have a connection to an equivalent candidate. We must be careful
1404 // to make sure that the origin port is included, even if it was pruned,
1405 // since that may be the only port that can create this connection.
1406 bool created = false;
1407 std::vector<PortInterface*>::reverse_iterator it;
1408 for (it = ports_.rbegin(); it != ports_.rend(); ++it) {
1409 if (CreateConnection(*it, remote_candidate, origin_port)) {
1410 if (*it == origin_port)
1411 created = true;
1412 }
1413 }
1414
1415 if ((origin_port != NULL) && !absl::c_linear_search(ports_, origin_port)) {
1416 if (CreateConnection(origin_port, remote_candidate, origin_port))
1417 created = true;
1418 }
1419
1420 // Remember this remote candidate so that we can add it to future ports.
1421 RememberRemoteCandidate(remote_candidate, origin_port);
1422
1423 return created;
1424}
1425
1426// Setup a connection object for the local and remote candidate combination.
1427// And then listen to connection object for changes.
1428bool P2PTransportChannel::CreateConnection(PortInterface* port,
1429 const Candidate& remote_candidate,
1430 PortInterface* origin_port) {
1431 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1432 if (!port->SupportsProtocol(remote_candidate.protocol())) {
1433 return false;
1434 }
1435
1436 if (field_trials_.skip_relay_to_non_relay_connections) {
1437 if ((port->Type() != remote_candidate.type()) &&
1438 (port->Type() == RELAY_PORT_TYPE ||
1439 remote_candidate.type() == RELAY_PORT_TYPE)) {
1440 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": skip creating connection "
1441 << port->Type() << " to " << remote_candidate.type();
1442 return false;
1443 }
1444 }
1445
1446 // Look for an existing connection with this remote address. If one is not
1447 // found or it is found but the existing remote candidate has an older
1448 // generation, then we can create a new connection for this address.
1449 Connection* connection = port->GetConnection(remote_candidate.address());
1450 if (connection == nullptr || connection->remote_candidate().generation() <
1451 remote_candidate.generation()) {
1452 // Don't create a connection if this is a candidate we received in a
1453 // message and we are not allowed to make outgoing connections.
1454 PortInterface::CandidateOrigin origin = GetOrigin(port, origin_port);
1455 if (origin == PortInterface::ORIGIN_MESSAGE && incoming_only_) {
1456 return false;
1457 }
1458 Connection* connection = port->CreateConnection(remote_candidate, origin);
1459 if (!connection) {
1460 return false;
1461 }
1462 AddConnection(connection);
1463 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
1464 << ": Created connection with origin: " << origin
1465 << ", total: " << connections().size();
1466 return true;
1467 }
1468
1469 // No new connection was created.
1470 // It is not legal to try to change any of the parameters of an existing
1471 // connection; however, the other side can send a duplicate candidate.
1472 if (!remote_candidate.IsEquivalent(connection->remote_candidate())) {
1473 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Attempt to change a remote candidate."
1474 " Existing remote candidate: "
1475 << connection->remote_candidate().ToSensitiveString()
1476 << "New remote candidate: "
1477 << remote_candidate.ToSensitiveString();
1478 }
1479 return false;
1480}
1481
1482bool P2PTransportChannel::FindConnection(const Connection* connection) const {
1483 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1484 return absl::c_linear_search(connections(), connection);
1485}
1486
1487uint32_t P2PTransportChannel::GetRemoteCandidateGeneration(
1488 const Candidate& candidate) {
1489 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1490 // If the candidate has a ufrag, use it to find the generation.
1491 if (!candidate.username().empty()) {
1492 uint32_t generation = 0;
1493 if (!FindRemoteIceFromUfrag(candidate.username(), &generation)) {
1494 // If the ufrag is not found, assume the next/future generation.
1495 generation = static_cast<uint32_t>(remote_ice_parameters_.size());
1496 }
1497 return generation;
1498 }
1499 // If candidate generation is set, use that.
1500 if (candidate.generation() > 0) {
1501 return candidate.generation();
1502 }
1503 // Otherwise, assume the generation from remote ice parameters.
1504 return remote_ice_generation();
1505}
1506
1507// Check if remote candidate is already cached.
1508bool P2PTransportChannel::IsDuplicateRemoteCandidate(
1509 const Candidate& candidate) {
1510 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1511 for (size_t i = 0; i < remote_candidates_.size(); ++i) {
1512 if (remote_candidates_[i].IsEquivalent(candidate)) {
1513 return true;
1514 }
1515 }
1516 return false;
1517}
1518
1519// Maintain our remote candidate list, adding this new remote one.
1520void P2PTransportChannel::RememberRemoteCandidate(
1521 const Candidate& remote_candidate,
1522 PortInterface* origin_port) {
1523 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1524 // Remove any candidates whose generation is older than this one. The
1525 // presence of a new generation indicates that the old ones are not useful.
1526 size_t i = 0;
1527 while (i < remote_candidates_.size()) {
1528 if (remote_candidates_[i].generation() < remote_candidate.generation()) {
1529 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Pruning candidate from old generation: "
1530 << remote_candidates_[i].address().ToSensitiveString();
1531 remote_candidates_.erase(remote_candidates_.begin() + i);
1532 } else {
1533 i += 1;
1534 }
1535 }
1536
1537 // Make sure this candidate is not a duplicate.
1538 if (IsDuplicateRemoteCandidate(remote_candidate)) {
1539 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Duplicate candidate: "
1540 << remote_candidate.ToSensitiveString();
1541 return;
1542 }
1543
1544 // Try this candidate for all future ports.
1545 remote_candidates_.push_back(RemoteCandidate(remote_candidate, origin_port));
1546}
1547
1548// Set options on ourselves is simply setting options on all of our available
1549// port objects.
1550int P2PTransportChannel::SetOption(rtc::Socket::Option opt, int value) {
1551 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1552 OptionMap::iterator it = options_.find(opt);
1553 if (it == options_.end()) {
1554 options_.insert(std::make_pair(opt, value));
1555 } else if (it->second == value) {
1556 return 0;
1557 } else {
1558 it->second = value;
1559 }
1560
1561 for (PortInterface* port : ports_) {
1562 int val = port->SetOption(opt, value);
1563 if (val < 0) {
1564 // Because this also occurs deferred, probably no point in reporting an
1565 // error
1566 RTC_LOG(WARNING) << "SetOption(" << opt << ", " << value
1567 << ") failed: " << port->GetError();
1568 }
1569 }
1570 return 0;
1571}
1572
1573bool P2PTransportChannel::GetOption(rtc::Socket::Option opt, int* value) {
1574 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1575
1576 const auto& found = options_.find(opt);
1577 if (found == options_.end()) {
1578 return false;
1579 }
1580 *value = found->second;
1581 return true;
1582}

1584int P2PTransportChannel::GetError() {
1585 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1586 return error_;
1587}
1588
1589// Send data to the other side, using our selected connection.
1590int P2PTransportChannel::SendPacket(const char* data,
1591 size_t len,
1592 const rtc::PacketOptions& options,
1593 int flags) {
1594 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1595 if (flags != 0) {
1596 error_ = EINVAL;
1597 return -1;
1598 }
1599 // If we don't think the connection is working yet, return ENOTCONN
1600 // instead of sending a packet that will probably be dropped.
1601 if (!ReadyToSend(selected_connection_)) {
1602 error_ = ENOTCONN;
1603 return -1;
1604 }
1605
1606 last_sent_packet_id_ = options.packet_id;
1607 rtc::PacketOptions modified_options(options);
1608 modified_options.info_signaled_after_sent.packet_type =
1609 rtc::PacketType::kData;
1610 int sent = selected_connection_->Send(data, len, modified_options);
1611 if (sent <= 0) {
1612 RTC_DCHECK(sent < 0);
1613 error_ = selected_connection_->GetError();
1614 }
1615 return sent;
1616}

1618bool P2PTransportChannel::GetStats(IceTransportStats* ice_transport_stats) {
1619 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1620 // Gather candidate and candidate pair stats.
1621 ice_transport_stats->candidate_stats_list.clear();
1622 ice_transport_stats->connection_infos.clear();
1623
1624 if (!allocator_sessions_.empty()) {
1625 allocator_session()->GetCandidateStatsFromReadyPorts(
1626 &ice_transport_stats->candidate_stats_list);
1627 }
1628
1629 // TODO(qingsi): Remove naming inconsistency for candidate pair/connection.
1630 for (Connection* connection : connections()) {
1631 ConnectionInfo stats = connection->stats();
1632 stats.local_candidate = SanitizeLocalCandidate(stats.local_candidate);
1633 stats.remote_candidate = SanitizeRemoteCandidate(stats.remote_candidate);
1634 stats.best_connection = (selected_connection_ == connection);
1635 ice_transport_stats->connection_infos.push_back(std::move(stats));
1636 connection->set_reported(true);
1637 }
1638
1639 ice_transport_stats->selected_candidate_pair_changes =
1640 selected_candidate_pair_changes_;
1641 return true;
1642}

1669

1717bool P2PTransportChannel::PresumedWritable(const Connection* conn) const {
1718 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1719 return (conn->write_state() == Connection::STATE_WRITE_INIT &&
1720 config_.presume_writable_when_fully_relayed &&
1721 conn->local_candidate().type() == RELAY_PORT_TYPE &&
1722 (conn->remote_candidate().type() == RELAY_PORT_TYPE ||
1723 conn->remote_candidate().type() == PRFLX_PORT_TYPE));
1724}
1725
1726// Sort the available connections to find the best one. We also monitor
1727// the number of available connections and the current state.
1728void P2PTransportChannel::SortConnectionsAndUpdateState(
1729 IceControllerEvent reason_to_sort) {
1730 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1731
1732 // Make sure the connection states are up-to-date since this affects how they
1733 // will be sorted.
1734 UpdateConnectionStates();
1735
1736 // Any changes after this point will require a re-sort.
1737 sort_dirty_ = false;
1738
1739 // If necessary, switch to the new choice. Note that |top_connection| doesn't
1740 // have to be writable to become the selected connection although it will
1741 // have higher priority if it is writable.
1742 MaybeSwitchSelectedConnection(
1743 reason_to_sort, ice_controller_->SortAndSwitchConnection(reason_to_sort));
1744
1745 // The controlled side can prune only if the selected connection has been
1746 // nominated because otherwise it may prune the connection that will be
1747 // selected by the controlling side.
1748 // TODO(honghaiz): This is not enough to prevent a connection from being
1749 // pruned too early because with aggressive nomination, the controlling side
1750 // will nominate every connection until it becomes writable.
1751 if (ice_role_ == ICEROLE_CONTROLLING ||
1752 (selected_connection_ && selected_connection_->nominated())) {
1753 PruneConnections();
1754 }
1755
1756 // Check if all connections are timedout.
1757 bool all_connections_timedout = true;
1758 for (const Connection* conn : connections()) {
1759 if (conn->write_state() != Connection::STATE_WRITE_TIMEOUT) {
1760 all_connections_timedout = false;
1761 break;
1762 }
1763 }
1764
1765 // Now update the writable state of the channel with the information we have
1766 // so far.
1767 if (all_connections_timedout) {
1768 HandleAllTimedOut();
1769 }
1770
1771 // Update the state of this channel.
1772 UpdateState();
1773
1774 // Also possibly start pinging.
1775 // We could start pinging if:
1776 // * The first connection was created.
1777 // * ICE credentials were provided.
1778 // * A TCP connection became connected.
1779 MaybeStartPinging();
1780}
1781
1782void P2PTransportChannel::PruneConnections() {
1783 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1784 std::vector<const Connection*> connections_to_prune =
1785 ice_controller_->PruneConnections();
1786 for (const Connection* conn : connections_to_prune) {
1787 FromIceController(conn)->Prune();
1788 }
1789}
1790
1791// Change the selected connection, and let listeners know.
1792void P2PTransportChannel::SwitchSelectedConnection(Connection* conn,
1793 IceControllerEvent reason) {
1794 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1795 // Note: if conn is NULL, the previous |selected_connection_| has been
1796 // destroyed, so don't use it.
1797 Connection* old_selected_connection = selected_connection_;
1798 selected_connection_ = conn;
1799 LogCandidatePairConfig(conn, webrtc::IceCandidatePairConfigType::kSelected);
1800 network_route_.reset();
1801 if (old_selected_connection) {
1802 old_selected_connection->set_selected(false);
1803 }
1804 if (selected_connection_) {
1805 ++nomination_;
1806 selected_connection_->set_selected(true);
1807 if (old_selected_connection) {
1808 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Previous selected connection: "
1809 << old_selected_connection->ToString();
1810 }
1811 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": New selected connection: "
1812 << selected_connection_->ToString();
1813 SignalRouteChange(this, selected_connection_->remote_candidate());
1814 // This is a temporary, but safe fix to webrtc issue 5705.
1815 // TODO(honghaiz): Make all ENOTCONN error routed through the transport
1816 // channel so that it knows whether the media channel is allowed to
1817 // send; then it will only signal ready-to-send if the media channel
1818 // has been disallowed to send.
1819 if (selected_connection_->writable() ||
1820 PresumedWritable(selected_connection_)) {
1821 SignalReadyToSend(this);
1822 }
1823
1824 network_route_.emplace(rtc::NetworkRoute());
1825 network_route_->connected = ReadyToSend(selected_connection_);
1826 network_route_->local = CreateRouteEndpointFromCandidate(
1827 /* local= */ true, selected_connection_->local_candidate(),
1828 /* uses_turn= */ selected_connection_->port()->Type() ==
1829 RELAY_PORT_TYPE);
1830 network_route_->remote = CreateRouteEndpointFromCandidate(
1831 /* local= */ false, selected_connection_->remote_candidate(),
1832 /* uses_turn= */ selected_connection_->remote_candidate().type() ==
1833 RELAY_PORT_TYPE);
1834
1835 network_route_->last_sent_packet_id = last_sent_packet_id_;
1836 network_route_->packet_overhead =
1837 selected_connection_->local_candidate().address().ipaddr().overhead() +
1838 GetProtocolOverhead(selected_connection_->local_candidate().protocol());
1839 } else {
1840 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": No selected connection";
1841 }
1842
1843 if (conn != nullptr && ice_role_ == ICEROLE_CONTROLLING &&
1844 ((field_trials_.send_ping_on_switch_ice_controlling &&
1845 old_selected_connection != nullptr) ||
1846 field_trials_.send_ping_on_selected_ice_controlling)) {
1847 PingConnection(conn);
1848 MarkConnectionPinged(conn);
1849 }
1850
1851 SignalNetworkRouteChanged(network_route_);
1852
1853 // Create event for candidate pair change.
1854 if (selected_connection_) {
1855 CandidatePairChangeEvent pair_change;
1856 pair_change.reason = reason.ToString();
1857 pair_change.selected_candidate_pair = *GetSelectedCandidatePair();
1858 pair_change.last_data_received_ms =
1859 selected_connection_->last_data_received();
1860
1861 if (old_selected_connection) {
1862 pair_change.estimated_disconnected_time_ms =
1863 ComputeEstimatedDisconnectedTimeMs(rtc::TimeMillis(),
1864 old_selected_connection);
1865 } else {
1866 pair_change.estimated_disconnected_time_ms = 0;
1867 }
1868
1869 SignalCandidatePairChanged(pair_change);
1870 }
1871
1872 ++selected_candidate_pair_changes_;
1873
1874 ice_controller_->SetSelectedConnection(selected_connection_);
1875}
1876
1877int64_t P2PTransportChannel::ComputeEstimatedDisconnectedTimeMs(
1878 int64_t now_ms,
1879 Connection* old_connection) {
1880 // TODO(jonaso): nicer keeps estimate of how frequently data _should_ be
1881 // received, this could be used to give better estimate (if needed).
1882 int64_t last_data_or_old_ping =
1883 std::max(old_connection->last_received(), last_data_received_ms_);
1884 return (now_ms - last_data_or_old_ping);
1885}
1886
1887// Warning: UpdateState should eventually be called whenever a connection
1888// is added, deleted, or the write state of any connection changes so that the
1889// transport controller will get the up-to-date channel state. However it
1890// should not be called too often; in the case that multiple connection states
1891// change, it should be called after all the connection states have changed. For
1892// example, we call this at the end of SortConnectionsAndUpdateState.
1893void P2PTransportChannel::UpdateState() {
1894 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1895 // If our selected connection is "presumed writable" (TURN-TURN with no
1896 // CreatePermission required), act like we're already writable to the upper
1897 // layers, so they can start media quicker.
1898 bool writable =
1899 selected_connection_ && (selected_connection_->writable() ||
1900 PresumedWritable(selected_connection_));
1901 SetWritable(writable);
1902
1903 bool receiving = false;
1904 for (const Connection* connection : connections()) {
1905 if (connection->receiving()) {
1906 receiving = true;
1907 break;
1908 }
1909 }
1910 SetReceiving(receiving);
1911
1912 IceTransportState state = ComputeState();
1913 webrtc::IceTransportState current_standardized_state =
1914 ComputeIceTransportState();
1915
1916 if (state_ != state) {
1917 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Transport channel state changed from "
1918 << static_cast<int>(state_) << " to "
1919 << static_cast<int>(state);
1920 // Check that the requested transition is allowed. Note that
1921 // P2PTransportChannel does not (yet) implement a direct mapping of the ICE
1922 // states from the standard; the difference is covered by
1923 // TransportController and PeerConnection.
1924 switch (state_) {
1925 case IceTransportState::STATE_INIT:
1926 // TODO(deadbeef): Once we implement end-of-candidates signaling,
1927 // we shouldn't go from INIT to COMPLETED.
1928 RTC_DCHECK(state == IceTransportState::STATE_CONNECTING ||
1929 state == IceTransportState::STATE_COMPLETED ||
1930 state == IceTransportState::STATE_FAILED);
1931 break;
1932 case IceTransportState::STATE_CONNECTING:
1933 RTC_DCHECK(state == IceTransportState::STATE_COMPLETED ||
1934 state == IceTransportState::STATE_FAILED);
1935 break;
1936 case IceTransportState::STATE_COMPLETED:
1937 // TODO(deadbeef): Once we implement end-of-candidates signaling,
1938 // we shouldn't go from COMPLETED to CONNECTING.
1939 // Though we *can* go from COMPlETED to FAILED, if consent expires.
1940 RTC_DCHECK(state == IceTransportState::STATE_CONNECTING ||
1941 state == IceTransportState::STATE_FAILED);
1942 break;
1943 case IceTransportState::STATE_FAILED:
1944 // TODO(deadbeef): Once we implement end-of-candidates signaling,
1945 // we shouldn't go from FAILED to CONNECTING or COMPLETED.
1946 RTC_DCHECK(state == IceTransportState::STATE_CONNECTING ||
1947 state == IceTransportState::STATE_COMPLETED);
1948 break;
1949 default:
1950 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1951 break;
1952 }
1953 state_ = state;
1954 SignalStateChanged(this);
1955 }
1956
1957 if (standardized_state_ != current_standardized_state) {
1958 standardized_state_ = current_standardized_state;
1959 SignalIceTransportStateChanged(this);
1960 }
1961}

1963void P2PTransportChannel::MaybeStopPortAllocatorSessions() {
1964 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1965 if (!IsGettingPorts()) {
1966 return;
1967 }
1968
1969 for (const auto& session : allocator_sessions_) {
1970 if (session->IsStopped()) {
1971 continue;
1972 }
1973 // If gathering continually, keep the last session running so that
1974 // it can gather candidates if the networks change.
1975 if (config_.gather_continually() && session == allocator_sessions_.back()) {
1976 session->ClearGettingPorts();
1977 } else {
1978 session->StopGettingPorts();
1979 }
1980 }
1981}

1991bool P2PTransportChannel::ReadyToSend(Connection* connection) const {
1992 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1993 // Note that we allow sending on an unreliable connection, because it's
1994 // possible that it became unreliable simply due to bad chance.
1995 // So this shouldn't prevent attempting to send media.
1996 return connection != nullptr &&
1997 (connection->writable() ||
1998 connection->write_state() == Connection::STATE_WRITE_UNRELIABLE ||
1999 PresumedWritable(connection));
2000}

2002// Handle queued up check-and-ping request
2003void P2PTransportChannel::CheckAndPing() {
2004 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2005 // Make sure the states of the connections are up-to-date (since this affects
2006 // which ones are pingable).
2007 UpdateConnectionStates();
2008
2009 auto result = ice_controller_->SelectConnectionToPing(last_ping_sent_ms_);
2010 int delay = result.recheck_delay_ms;
2011
2012 if (result.connection.value_or(nullptr)) {
2013 Connection* conn = FromIceController(*result.connection);
2014 PingConnection(conn);
2015 MarkConnectionPinged(conn);
2016 }
2017
2018 network_thread_->PostDelayedTask(
2019 ToQueuedTask(task_safety_, [this]() { CheckAndPing(); }), delay);
2020}

2040// Apart from sending ping from |conn| this method also updates
2041// |use_candidate_attr| and |nomination| flags. One of the flags is set to
2042// nominate |conn| if this channel is in CONTROLLING.
2043void P2PTransportChannel::PingConnection(Connection* conn) {
2044 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2045 bool use_candidate_attr = false;
2046 uint32_t nomination = 0;
2047 if (ice_role_ == ICEROLE_CONTROLLING) {
2048 bool renomination_supported = ice_parameters_.renomination &&
2049 !remote_ice_parameters_.empty() &&
2050 remote_ice_parameters_.back().renomination;
2051 if (renomination_supported) {
2052 nomination = GetNominationAttr(conn);
2053 } else {
2054 use_candidate_attr = GetUseCandidateAttr(conn);
2055 }
2056 }
2057 conn->set_nomination(nomination);
2058 conn->set_use_candidate_attr(use_candidate_attr);
2059 last_ping_sent_ms_ = rtc::TimeMillis();
2060 conn->Ping(last_ping_sent_ms_);
2061}

2064 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2065 return (conn == selected_connection_) ? nomination_ : 0;

2075// When a connection's state changes, we need to figure out who to use as
2076// the selected connection again. It could have become usable, or become
2077// unusable.
2078void P2PTransportChannel::OnConnectionStateChange(Connection* connection) {
2079 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2080
2081 // May stop the allocator session when at least one connection becomes
2082 // strongly connected after starting to get ports and the local candidate of
2083 // the connection is at the latest generation. It is not enough to check
2084 // that the connection becomes weakly connected because the connection may be
2085 // changing from (writable, receiving) to (writable, not receiving).
2086 if (field_trials_.stop_gather_on_strongly_connected) {
2087 bool strongly_connected = !connection->weak();
2088 bool latest_generation = connection->local_candidate().generation() >=
2089 allocator_session()->generation();
2090 if (strongly_connected && latest_generation) {
2091 MaybeStopPortAllocatorSessions();
2092 }
2093 }
2094 // We have to unroll the stack before doing this because we may be changing
2095 // the state of connections while sorting.
2096 RequestSortAndStateUpdate(
2097 IceControllerEvent::CONNECT_STATE_CHANGE); // "candidate pair state
2098 // changed");
2099}
2100
2101// When a connection is removed, edit it out, and then update our best
2102// connection.
2103void P2PTransportChannel::OnConnectionDestroyed(Connection* connection) {
2104 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2105
2106 // Note: the previous selected_connection_ may be destroyed by now, so don't
2107 // use it.
2108
2109 // Remove this connection from the list.
2110 ice_controller_->OnConnectionDestroyed(connection);
2111
2112 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Removed connection " << connection
2113 << " (" << connections().size() << " remaining)";
2114
2115 // If this is currently the selected connection, then we need to pick a new
2116 // one. The call to SortConnectionsAndUpdateState will pick a new one. It
2117 // looks at the current selected connection in order to avoid switching
2118 // between fairly similar ones. Since this connection is no longer an option,
2119 // we can just set selected to nullptr and re-choose a best assuming that
2120 // there was no selected connection.
2121 if (selected_connection_ == connection) {
2122 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Selected connection destroyed. Will choose a new one.";
2123 IceControllerEvent reason =
2124 IceControllerEvent::SELECTED_CONNECTION_DESTROYED;
2125 SwitchSelectedConnection(nullptr, reason);
2126 RequestSortAndStateUpdate(reason);
2127 } else {
2128 // If a non-selected connection was destroyed, we don't need to re-sort but
2129 // we do need to update state, because we could be switching to "failed" or
2130 // "completed".
2131 UpdateState();
2132 }
2133}

2135// When a port is destroyed, remove it from our list of ports to use for
2136// connection attempts.
2137void P2PTransportChannel::OnPortDestroyed(PortInterface* port) {
2138 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2139
2140 ports_.erase(std::remove(ports_.begin(), ports_.end(), port), ports_.end());
2141 pruned_ports_.erase(
2142 std::remove(pruned_ports_.begin(), pruned_ports_.end(), port),
2143 pruned_ports_.end());
2144 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Removed port because it is destroyed: " << ports_.size()
2145 << " remaining";
2146}

2160void P2PTransportChannel::OnCandidatesRemoved(
2161 PortAllocatorSession* session,
2162 const std::vector<Candidate>& candidates) {
2163 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2164 // Do not signal candidate removals if continual gathering is not enabled, or
2165 // if this is not the last session because an ICE restart would have signaled
2166 // the remote side to remove all candidates in previous sessions.
2167 if (!config_.gather_continually() || session != allocator_session()) {
2168 return;
2169 }
2170
2171 std::vector<Candidate> candidates_to_remove;
2172 for (Candidate candidate : candidates) {
2173 candidate.set_transport_name(transport_name());
2174 candidates_to_remove.push_back(candidate);
2175 }
2176 SignalCandidatesRemoved(this, candidates_to_remove);
2177}

2179void P2PTransportChannel::PruneAllPorts() {
2180 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2181 pruned_ports_.insert(pruned_ports_.end(), ports_.begin(), ports_.end());
2182 ports_.clear();
2183}
2184
2185bool P2PTransportChannel::PrunePort(PortInterface* port) {
2186 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2187 auto it = absl::c_find(ports_, port);
2188 // Don't need to do anything if the port has been deleted from the port list.
2189 if (it == ports_.end()) {
2190 return false;
2191 }
2192 ports_.erase(it);
2193 pruned_ports_.push_back(port);
2194 return true;
2195}

2197// We data is available, let listeners know
2198void P2PTransportChannel::OnReadPacket(Connection* connection,
2199 const char* data,
2200 size_t len,
2201 int64_t packet_time_us) {
2202 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2203
2204 if (connection == selected_connection_) {
2205 // Let the client know of an incoming packet
2206 RTC_DCHECK(connection->last_data_received() >= last_data_received_ms_);
2207 last_data_received_ms_ =
2208 std::max(last_data_received_ms_, connection->last_data_received());
2209 SignalReadPacket(this, data, len, packet_time_us, 0);
2210 return;
2211 }
2212
2213 // Do not deliver, if packet doesn't belong to the correct transport channel.
2214 if (!FindConnection(connection))
2215 return;
2216
2217 RTC_DCHECK(connection->last_data_received() >= last_data_received_ms_);
2218 last_data_received_ms_ =
2219 std::max(last_data_received_ms_, connection->last_data_received());
2220
2221 // Let the client know of an incoming packet
2222 SignalReadPacket(this, data, len, packet_time_us, 0);
2223
2224 // May need to switch the sending connection based on the receiving media path
2225 // if this is the controlled side.
2226 if (ice_role_ == ICEROLE_CONTROLLED) {
2227 MaybeSwitchSelectedConnection(connection,
2228 IceControllerEvent::DATA_RECEIVED);
2229 }
2230}

2275Candidate P2PTransportChannel::SanitizeRemoteCandidate(
2276 const Candidate& c) const {
2277 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2278 // If the remote endpoint signaled us an mDNS candidate, we assume it
2279 // is supposed to be sanitized.
2280 bool use_hostname_address = absl::EndsWith(c.address().hostname(), LOCAL_TLD);
2281 // Remove the address for prflx remote candidates. See
2282 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcicecandidatestats.
2283 use_hostname_address |= c.type() == PRFLX_PORT_TYPE;
2284 return c.ToSanitizedCopy(use_hostname_address,
2285 false /* filter_related_address */);
